"At the highroad turn leftward a little way to Bacon Lane on the right ; where pass through a swing-gate to a field-path. Follow this path (which crosses another) for a full half-mile into a road. There turn leftward, and go on till you come to an open green. At the further side of this, at a transverse road, you will find, just to the left of a brook, but well to the right of the Green Man, a bit of field-railing used as the stile of two field-paths. Follow the right-hand path over several fields into the angle of & green lane, where go straight through to another angle for a continuing path, leading to a short lane, with a road- crossing beyond. There go straight through to an opposite lane, with the Rose and Crown on your left, till you reach a field-gate and stile beside a cluster of cottages, whence"